# Anvil daemon environment — see arch §3 (auth & billing constraint).
#
# Generate the OAuth token with:  claude setup-token
# This authenticates Claude Code against your Max subscription (NOT metered API billing).
CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=

# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY and ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN MUST NOT be set.
# They outrank the OAuth token in Claude Code's auth precedence and would silently
# switch billing to metered pay-per-token. The daemon refuses to start if either is set.

# Optional overrides:
# ANVIL_PORT=7701
# ANVIL_STATE_DIR=~/.anvil
# ANVIL_BUDGET_WARN=0.8
# ANVIL_BUDGET_SOFTSTOP=0.95

# Adversarial multi-model planning (OpenRouter). After Claude writes a plan, competing OpenRouter
# models adversarially critique and score it; the strongest objection is surfaced on the WorkUnit.
# Each critic runs as an AGENT: it reads the actual repo (read-only list_dir/read_file/grep, confined
# to the env's repo root) to check the plan against real code, so this makes several tool round-trips
# per model and costs more than a single call. This is a DIFFERENT provider with its own key — it does
# NOT go through the Agent SDK, so it's unaffected by the ANTHROPIC_* guard above. The panel is SKIPPED
# entirely when the key is absent.
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...
# ANVIL_ADVERSARIAL_MODELS=openai/gpt-5-codex,z-ai/glm-5.2
# ANVIL_ADVERSARIAL=0   # kill switch: disable the panel even when a key is set
#
# Optional: pin the panel to one OpenRouter provider (slug, e.g. "deepinfra"). GLM has no explicit
# cache_control, so keeping the critic on a single cheap-cache-read provider is what actually keeps its
# implicit prompt cache warm across the agent loop's rounds. Sent with allow_fallbacks, so a model that
# provider can't serve still routes normally. Leave unset for OpenRouter's default routing.
# ANVIL_ADVERSARIAL_PROVIDER=deepinfra
